  "prompt": "Why did Quora limit question details to 300 words?",
  "response": "Quora implemented a limit on the length of question details to 300 words in order to improve overall user experience and ensure that questions remain clear and concise. Long, detailed questions can sometimes become unwieldy and difficult to read, which may lead to fewer responses or decreased engagement. By limiting the word count, Quora encourages users to focus on the most important aspects of their question and promote a more direct and focused dialogue. This can help in maintaining a higher quality of content and make it easier for users to navigate and find relevant information on the platform.",
